Dedicated host allow you to provision Ec2 instances  on physical  server fully dedicated d
for your use

Dedicated Host Setting :
\_Name tag:   Name of your Dedicated host
\_Instance family: Specify the instance family to be specified by the dedicated hosts
\_Enabel > Support multiple instance type: Launch different instance type  from the same instance family
                                   on the dedicated host 
\_Instance type : The instance type that can be launched  onto dedicated hosts
\_Availability Zone : The availability zone  in which  the dedicated host is located 
\_Outpost ARN :      Unique ID of your physical AWS rack sitting in your datacenter AWS uses it to deploy
                     resources onto the correct outpost 
\_Instance auto-placement : Disabling auto-placement will preserve the dedicated host for targeted 
                             Launch requests .enabling auto placement  will allow untargeted (no host ID
                            (no host ID specified ) launch requests to succed 
\_Host recovery : Automatically restart your instance on to a new replacement host if your 
                  current  host is unreachable  due to permanent failure 
\_Quantity: The number of Dedicated hosts you'd like to purchase for this configuration 
\_Tags-  Optional 
